1
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:53,120
Don't go! Don't go!

2
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,559
Dear.

3
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,360
- Dad.
- Dear.

4
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:06,520
You're going to stay with me forever.

5
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,839
This is bad!

6
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:15,040
An island!
The ship's gonna crash into the island!

7
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:22,480
You'll all die.

8
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,440
There's no way you can help Kaimook.

9
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,200
‎What are you doing?

10
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:10,720
We have to get off this ship
before it crashes into the island.

11
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,039
Huh? We're going to jump into the sea?

12
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,439
Yes.

13
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:18,439
But if we jump, we'll die anyway.

14
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,240
We're in the middle of the sea.

15
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,200
I can't. I'm scared.

16
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,520
Is that a ship?

17
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,480
Let me see.

18
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,600
It looks like a pirate ship.

19
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,560
Judging by its direction,
it seems to have come from Skull Island.

20
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,039
Or maybe
they attacked the research center.

21
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,600
Could they be the reason
we haven't been able to contact anyone?

22
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,079
Mr. Phum,

23
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,760
get us closer.

24
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,159
What about Kaimook?

25
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,400
Where is Kaimook?

26
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,960
And who's steering the ship?

27
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,080
This is bad.

28
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,440
There's an island ahead.

29
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,839
The ship's going to crash into it.

30
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,600
It's not slowing down at all.

31
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,559
Look! There's a boat coming this way!

32
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,239
- Help!
- Help!

33
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,919
- This way!
- Help!

34
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,199
Dad!

35
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,679
Hurry and get down here.

36
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,759
The ship's about to crash into the island.

37
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:40,959
This way!

38
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,080
Dad!

39
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,840
Hurry! We don't have much time!

40
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,560
Na?!

41
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,800
- Mana, keep this distance.
- Okay.

42
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,320
Prachaya,

43
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,800
- you go first.
- Okay.

44
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,280
Come down slowly.

45
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,760
- Take my hand.
- Alright.

46
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,240
‎Come on!

47
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,360
Thank you so much.

48
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:20,799
Dara, come on.

49
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,680
Dara! Come!

50
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:26,000
Ms. Da, your turn.

51
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,519
No, I'm scared.

52
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:31,320
I've never climbed
a rope ladder like this before.

53
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,679
Dara!

54
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,680
- Come!
- Come down!

55
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:39,199
Dara! Come down!

56
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:41,159
Why won't Dara come down?

57
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,560
She's too scared. She won't come down.

58
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,079
Scared?

59
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,120
What are we going to do?

60
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:48,039
Come down!

61
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,759
Professor Prachaya,

62
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,479
come take over the boat for me.

63
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,280
- Okay.
- Hurry up.

64
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,080
Da, come down.

65
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,640
Na.

66
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,760
Go help her.

67
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,080
Be careful.

68
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,039
Da.

69
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,599
Na.

70
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:23,600
You're okay, right?

71
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:34,919
Go.

72
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,840
And don't come back to this island again.

73
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,600
Dad.

74
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,760
Please help that woman.

75
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,120
Thon, come!

76
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,840
Take my hand.

77
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,960
Come on.

78
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,480
Thon!

79
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,480
Thon, give me your hand.

80
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,840
I won't let you go. Give me your hand!

81
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,720
Come on!

82
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,319
Thon, how are you?

83
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,360
Are you alright?

84
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,400
I'm alright.

85
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,959
Mr. Thon,

86
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,280
what about Kaimook? Where is she?

87
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,000
Kaimook is still on the island.

88
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,399
We need to help her.

89
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,320
What?!

90
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,800
Dear.

91
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,240
How are you feeling?

92
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:21,160
Why am I here?

93
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:25,240
- I'll go save Kaimook.
- Hey.

94
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,600
Save yourself first.

95
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,959
What are you doing?

96
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,000
I'm going to help our daughter.

97
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,519
No need.

98
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:38,440
Mr. Phum and Na already went to help her.

99
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:42,400
Don't worry.

100
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,639
If you keep stressing yourself out,
you'll collapse again.

101
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,960
Na's not a child anymore.

102
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,080
He'll definitely bring Mook back safely.

103
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:56,040
Just two people,
what can they possibly do?

104
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,799
Before you woke up,

105
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,879
the MP who's friends
with Mr. Phum came to visit.

106
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,839
He told me the police
had already been contacted

107
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,880
and sent to Skull Island.

108
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,719
Please, don't worry.

109
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,160
Get some rest.

110
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:12,000
Mook will be safe.

111
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,160
Trust me.

112
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,600
Alright, now get some rest.

113
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,720
Don't be stubborn.

114
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,800
Be careful, everyone.

115
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,759
Don't be afraid, Da.

116
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,959
Whether it's a person or a ghost,

117
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:01,000
I won't let anyone hurt you.

118
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,960
Okay.

119
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,040
You're very lucky

120
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,040
to have a boyfriend like Mr. Mana.

121
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,040
Are you ready?

122
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:22,560
Let's go.

123
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,320
Mr. Narathon.

124
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,000
Mr. Phum.

125
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:52,440
- Kaimook.
- Mook.

126
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,919
- Kaimook.
- Na.

127
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,560
Don't go, Kaimook.

128
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,640
What is this?

129
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,720
They're not human.

130
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,680
Don't fall for them.

131
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,120
Kaimook.

132
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,240
Focus.

133
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,400
I believe you'll know
which side isn't human.

134
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:21,999
Dear,

135
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,520
I'm thirsty.

136
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,599
Oh? You're on IV fluids right now.

137
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,240
Can you really drink?

138
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,999
I'm not sure either.

139
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,880
Can you ask the nurse for me?

140
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,280
But I really am thirsty.

141
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,440
Than wait here a moment.

142
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,560
Kaimook.

143
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,399
Yes, Dad?

144
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,440
<i>Na, can you hear me?</i>

145
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:27,679
You called at the perfect time, Dad.

146
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:29,279
<i>Did you find your sister yet?</i>

147
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,639
Yes. She's safe.

148
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,840
I'll bring her back as soon as possible.

149
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,960
I'll talk to you later.

150
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,760
Kaimook, come here.

151
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,280
Come, Mook.

152
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,240
Don't, Mook. Don't trust them.

153
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,000
Come on.

154
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,598
You're so smart, Mook.

155
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,960
How did you know?

156
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,358
There's no phone signal here.

157
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:31,639
And those people
didn't make any footsteps.

158
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:34,400
But I could clearly hear ours.

159
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:37,080
You're smart, Mook.

160
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,560
Be careful, everyone.

161
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,800
You're smart, Kaimook.

162
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,839
But no matter how smart you are,

163
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:21,440
you'll never escape me, Kaimook.

164
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:31,360
Fire!

165
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,160
Thon!

166
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,160
Dad.

167
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:38,400
Mr. Thon.

168
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,520
Are you okay?

169
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,680
Narathon.

170
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,520
Are you alright?

171
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:52,960
Are you alright, son?

172
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,400
I'm alright.

173
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:00,559
You should all get back to the mainland.

174
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,559
I'll send officers to escort your boat.

175
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,400
We'll handle the rest.

176
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,279
Okay.

177
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,879
Let's go, everyone.

178
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:10,559
No one got hurt, right?

179
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,560
- No.
- Let's go.

180
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:24,319
We searched everywhere, sir.

181
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,520
But there's no sign
of anyone else left on the island.

182
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,279
How is that possible?
There were several of them.

183
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:30,360
Well,

184
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,759
the research center staff told me

185
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,200
that...

186
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,040
those were ghosts.

187
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,280
- Keep searching.
- Yes, sir.

188
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,400
Excuse me.

189
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:43,920
Thank you.

190
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,120
Are you okay?

191
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,119
I'm okay now.

192
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,760
I just feel a bit cold.

193
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:16,240
Thank you for coming to save me.

194
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,640
Of course, I had to come.

195
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,040
Drink some water first.

196
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,240
Thank you.

197
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,040
Thank you.

198
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,240
Na, are you cold?

199
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:41,080
I'm perfectly fine.

200
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,360
Are you worried I'll get cold?

201
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,040
Thank you.

202
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,560
Why didn't you kill them?

203
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:14,240
Because she's your daughter, isn't she?

204
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:24,439
This is Mr. Sumet, the hospital director.

205
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,799
He's Mr. Phum's friend.

206
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:28,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

207
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:32,200
You seem much better now, Mr. Mek.

208
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:35,319
Thank you so much

209
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:37,759
for taking care of everything.

210
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:40,359
Mr. Phum instructed me to take

211
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,640
very good care of both you and Mrs. Mhai.

212
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:45,479
Also, the officers found your daughter.

213
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,839
She's safe.

214
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:49,160
She's on the way back.

215
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:51,879
Alright.

216
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,279
If there's nothing else, please excuse me.

217
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:54,960
- Thank you so much.
- Goodbye.

218
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,519
Dear,

219
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:01,320
are you feeling relieved now?

220
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:05,399
Then get plenty of rest.

221
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,640
You'll recover fast.
Kaimook will be here soon.

222
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:15,879
Dad! Dad, can you hear me?

223
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,000
Dad!

224
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,000
Mr. Phum's awake.

225
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:22,920
Mr. Phum's awake.

226
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,120
What happened?

227
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:40,560
You must've been exhausted.
You fainted and fell into the water.

228
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,240
Mr. Phum, is something wrong?

229
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,680
Who went down to save me?

230
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:03,120
I did.

231
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,920
Did you see anyone else?

232
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:13,960
What are you talking about?

233
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,280
Are you feeling unwell, Mr. Phum?

234
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:34,560
No.

235
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:36,840
I must really just be exhausted.

236
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:46,320
- Mook.
- Mook!

237
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,040
Dad, Mom.

238
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,120
Mook.

239
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:54,679
Na.

240
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:56,240
You're safe, right?

241
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,880
You're alright now.

242
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:01,440
- Everyone's safe, sir.
- Thank you.

243
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:04,440
Thank you.

244
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:06,759
Let me treat you to a meal
when we have time.

245
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:08,079
Don't mention it.

246
00:30:08,080 --> 00:30:09,559
You should all go home and rest first.

247
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:11,399
There's still a lot left
to deal with here.

248
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,200
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

249
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:17,920
Mr. Phum,

250
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,599
thank you so much

251
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:22,560
for helping us with everything.

252
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:27,240
Thank you for everything.

253
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,199
It's nothing.

254
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:31,279
You should hurry
and take Kaimook home to rest.

255
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:32,760
She looks exhausted.

256
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:39,159
Thank you so much, Mr. Phum.

257
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:42,079
And thank you for this shirt too.

258
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:44,120
It's fine. Just wear it for now.

259
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,199
Let's go home.

260
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,440
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

261
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,319
Dad, Mom,

262
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:53,840
you can go first. I'll follow you shortly.

263
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,800
Okay.

264
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:58,519
We're going now, Mr. Phum.

265
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,120
Good luck.

266
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:01,720
Let's go.

267
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:11,799
Thank you, Professor.

268
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,119
You're welcome.

269
00:31:13,120 --> 00:31:14,360
See you later, Kaimook.

270
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,520
Thank you.

271
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:23,880
You're welcome.

272
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:26,080
Take care of yourself.

273
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:33,800
I'll go now.

274
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:36,239
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

275
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:38,040
- See you later.
- Okay.

276
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,200
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

277
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,079
Mana, you're a very good captain.

278
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:46,479
Without you,
we might not have made it in time.

279
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,679
Thank you.

280
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,599
- Here's your bag.
- Thank you.

281
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:50,719
- Goodbye, Mr. Phum.
- Goodbye.

282
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:52,760
Goodbye. Good luck.

283
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,920
Let's go home too.

284
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:03,160
I'm going with Prachaya.

285
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,400
You should go home.

286
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:13,760
Excuse me, sir.

287
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:16,040
I'll wait over there.

288
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,080
- Goodbye, Mr. Phum.
- Goodbye.

289
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:32,080
What's gotten into you again?

290
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,480
I've always been like this.

291
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:42,240
If you think saving me

292
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:45,960
will change how I feel about you,

293
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,560
then you're wrong.

294
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:53,640
Fine.

295
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,879
I helped you from the island.

296
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,840
You saved me when I fell into the water.

297
00:32:58,960 --> 00:32:59,880
So we're even now.

298
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:28,480
Let's go.

299
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:30,560
What about your father?

300
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,160
We go our separate ways.

301
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:36,319
Don't you think
you're being a little too cold?

302
00:33:36,320 --> 00:33:38,119
Your dad
went all the way there to help us.

303
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:40,640
Otherwise, we might not have
survived those damn ghosts.

304
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,280
Thon.

305
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:49,120
Thon.

306
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:23,319
Don't turn around.

307
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:24,840
The moment you turn around, you die!

308
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:26,839
Don't. Don't turn around.

309
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:29,360
Don't turn around.

310
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:36,839
Don't.

311
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:38,158
You again?

312
00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:39,760
Go on. Get lost.

313
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:43,320
Go.

314
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,840
Get lost.

315
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,400
Go.

316
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,839
A woman. A woman!

317
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,080
A woman...

318
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:58,840
A woman fell into the sea!

319
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:03,439
The woman's hands were tied.

320
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:04,640
What woman?

321
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:07,759
I'm asking you.

322
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:11,999
A woman.

323
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,120
A woman fell into the sea.

324
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,359
What did you see?!

325
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:26,000
What do you know? Say it!

326
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:27,600
Tell me!

327
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,399
Is she dead?

328
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:18,279
Does anyone know this woman?
Any relatives here?

329
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:19,879
- No.
- I don't know her.

330
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:22,439
Help her first. Start CPR.

331
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,520
I don't know how.

332
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:33,999
Call an ambulance.

333
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,000
Yes, call them.

334
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:44,080
She might be dead already.

335
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:45,920
Sir,

336
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:49,759
stop trying. She's dead.

337
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:51,520
Doesn't look like she'll make it.

338
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:55,040
Poor her.

339
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,320
Then please report this to the police.

340
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:09,560
Call them.

341
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:26,600
She's awake!

342
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:39,239
Hey.

343
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:42,199
- I can't believe it.
- Hey.

344
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,479
How are you feeling?

345
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:44,400
Hey.

346
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:45,960
Hey.

347
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:47,720
It's unbelievable.

348
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,839
Hey.

349
00:37:58,840 --> 00:37:59,879
- Hey.
- Hey.

350
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,280
Hey.

351
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:19,279
Let's stay here for a night first.

352
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,680
We'll go back to Bangkok tomorrow.

353
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:23,360
So you and Da won't be too tired.

354
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,239
That's good.

355
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:28,759
But don't worry, Dad.

356
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,400
I'm okay.

357
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:33,079
If it were me,

358
00:38:33,080 --> 00:38:36,480
I would've died of a heart attack
before anyone came to save me.

359
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,320
You did great, Mook.

360
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,799
After facing
something supernatural like that,

361
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,560
if you hadn't stayed calm,
you wouldn't have survived.

362
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:56,319
Da, thank you so much

363
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,239
for not abandoning me.

364
00:38:58,240 --> 00:39:00,440
I didn't want to stay.

365
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:02,439
But Mr. Thon

366
00:39:02,440 --> 00:39:04,079
refused to give up.

367
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:06,119
He kept insisting
we had to save you no matter what.

368
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:07,440
So I had no choice but to stay.

369
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:13,119
That's why old people always say.

370
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:16,279
You only see someone's true nature

371
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:18,640
when disaster strikes.

372
00:39:19,240 --> 00:39:22,000
That's true.
Mr. Narathon really is a good person.

373
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:27,479
I think we should all go get some rest.

374
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:29,599
None of you slept all night.

375
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:30,520
Let's go.

376
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:44,080
Then I'm going now.

377
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:49,600
Na,

378
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,680
I have something
I want to talk to you about.

379
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:57,960
Sure.

380
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:09,520
Da,

381
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:11,880
is something wrong?

382
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,760
You seem troubled.

383
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,600
I want to apologize to you.

384
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,759
You didn't do anything wrong to me.

385
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:32,480
Why are you apologizing?

386
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,680
I treated you badly in many ways.

387
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,840
Oh, come on.

388
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:41,959
Those were small things.

389
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:43,040
Don't overthink it.

390
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:45,800
I never took them to heart.

391
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:51,960
Da,

392
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,360
we've known each other
for a very long time.

393
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:59,560
You can't expect us
to be all sweet and romantic.

394
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:02,200
I know

395
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:04,520
I'm not a romantic person myself.

396
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:07,920
Sometimes maybe you get bored of me
or annoyed with me.

397
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:10,840
I understand.

398
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:17,679
But remember this.

399
00:41:17,680 --> 00:41:18,880
I've always loved you

400
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:21,479
and wished the best for you

401
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:24,120
from the very first day until now.

402
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,200
Yes.

403
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,279
I know.

404
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:31,120
I probably won't ever find anyone
who could love me as much as you do.

405
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:35,959
I'm sorry

406
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,120
for everything I've done.

407
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:40,520
It's okay.

408
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,120
Family members, please wait outside.

409
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:19,199
Oh, Mr. Phum.

410
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:21,479
- Hello.
- Oh, Kang, hello.

411
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,000
I'm really glad to see you.

412
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:25,080
My respect, Venerable Sir.

413
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:26,960
Blessings upon you.

414
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,159
Is this the Mr. Phum

415
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:31,999
you always tell me about?

416
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,120
Yes.

417
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:38,080
Kang admires you very much.

418
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:41,479
He says you're kind and generous.

419
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:44,360
He even wishes he had a father like you.

420
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:48,240
Kang is a very good kid too.
Hardworking and very smart.

421
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:53,719
Thank you for not looking down
on a temple boy like him.

422
00:42:53,720 --> 00:42:55,080
‎Of course.

423
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:58,040
Are you unwell, Venerable Sir?

424
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:00,920
Just a little.

425
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:04,560
I think

426
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:06,999
you feel strangely familiar to me.

427
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:08,480
It's like we've met before.

428
00:43:11,720 --> 00:43:13,600
No meeting between people

429
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:15,960
is ever coincidence.

430
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:19,560
And feeling familiar is nothing strange.

431
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:23,919
If we haven't
shared merit together before,

432
00:43:23,920 --> 00:43:26,439
then perhaps we once shared karma.

433
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:28,400
That's why we meet again.

434
00:43:30,320 --> 00:43:31,519
Yes.

435
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:32,959
Did you go to Thon's house today?

436
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:34,399
Not yet, sir.

437
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:37,240
Sir, the doctor is asking for you
in the examination room.

438
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:40,280
Please excuse me. See you later, Kang.

439
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:49,519
Get out!

440
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:51,440
- Get out! Stay away from me!
- Please calm down.

441
00:43:52,160 --> 00:43:53,759
I said get out!

442
00:43:53,760 --> 00:43:55,159
Get out!

443
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:57,279
What is this? I said get out!

444
00:43:57,280 --> 00:43:59,039
Get out!

445
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:00,679
What is this?!

446
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:02,239
Don't pull it out.

447
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:03,919
You're still weak.

448
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:05,399
You need the IV fluids.

449
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,119
I said I'm not sick.

450
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:09,079
Calm down.

451
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:10,879
Everyone's trying to help you.

452
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:12,400
What are you doing?

453
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:20,760
I'm fine.

454
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:22,799
You drowned.

455
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:24,879
Your heart even stopped beating.

456
00:44:24,880 --> 00:44:26,839
Look at yourself.

457
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:28,119
You're pale as a corpse.

458
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:29,680
And you still say you're fine?

459
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:54,960
Back then, I was just
as scared as you were.

460
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:57,560
<i>I was scared of losing you.</i>

461
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:01,560
Tell me!

462
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:04,240
Who threw that woman into the sea?

463
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:11,599
Pong.

464
00:45:11,600 --> 00:45:14,200
Mr. Phum, I...

465
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:17,959
I have to find out who that woman is

466
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:19,999
and why she hates my father enough

467
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:22,120
to want him dead.

468
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:53,520
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
